# GitHub CODEOWNERS — review assignments
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-customization/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# When a PR touches a path, listed owners are auto-requested for review.
# The most-specific matching rule wins (later entries override earlier ones
# for the same path).

# --- Default owner for the whole repo ---
* @darkhunt-security/engineering

# --- Higher-risk areas: explicit re-listing for visibility ---
# Same owner today; the per-path entries make it easy to add a security
# sub-team or specific maintainer later without editing the default rule.

# Data masking is the security-relevant core of this SDK.
/src/masking/                       @darkhunt-security/engineering
/src/masking/rules/                 @darkhunt-security/engineering
/src/masking/validators/            @darkhunt-security/engineering

# Exporter handles all outbound network + auth.
/src/exporter.ts                    @darkhunt-security/engineering

# CI, publish flow, and policy files.
/.github/                           @darkhunt-security/engineering
/sonar-project.properties           @darkhunt-security/engineering
/renovate.json                      @darkhunt-security/engineering

# Public-facing policy / licensing — review carefully when changed.
/LICENSE                            @darkhunt-security/engineering
/NOTICE                             @darkhunt-security/engineering
/SECURITY.md                        @darkhunt-security/engineering
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md                 @darkhunt-security/engineering
/CONTRIBUTING.md                    @darkhunt-security/engineering
